Manchester City have been limited to a net transfer spend of £49million in the last two transfer windows . 
  Manuel Pellegrini is hoping the restrictions will be lifted at the end of the season . 
  The club breached financial fairplay regulations by breaching £205m wage bill . 
  City have lost £23million this season and have been restricted to £49m net spend . 
  The champions have been linked with Raheem Sterling and Kevin de Bruyne . 
 